Tel Aviv  –  An Israeli Court South of Tel Aviv on Monday convicted a Jewish settler of murdering a Palestinian couple and their baby boy in July 2015 arson attack, Kan Israel Radio reported. Amiram Ben-Uliel, in his 20s, threw a firebomb into the home of a Palestinian family in the the Northern West Bank village of Duma, near Nablus. Ali Dawabshe, 18 months old, and his parents burned to death as their room caught fire while they were sleeping. The toddler’s 4-year-old brother was severely injured. (dpa/NAN)